                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No.2812.00/2742.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Extracts.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-05T14:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The State is a unit against the Federal Government, and open war will follow
                    entrance any Federal troops into the State. Control of leaders over soldiers
                    problematical and civil authorities helpless.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
